This is a linux Kernel Device Driver for a simple Inter Process Communication device. This device can be used to pass strings of 4 characters long between two processes. It has made use of  the Kernel "comlpetions" functionality. You can test it as follows .

Step 1:
	Compile the module. This can be done by a simple command "make".
Step 2:
	Insert the module. This can be done by "make ins"
Step 3:
	Create the code for two read and write processes. The code is given as read.c and write.c. Compile it using "make exe"
Step 4:
	Create the device by using "make dev"
Step 5:
	Execute the read and write executables.
